	(115932,1,'2019-11-22 15:10:47','2019-11-22 21:10:47','Prep Girls Hoops Colorado is excited to announce that we have released the first update to the most comprehensive prospect rankings for the 2020 graduating class.\n\nAt Prep Girls Hoops, we put a lot of time, thought and networking into building our player rankings. Colorado’s rankings are compiled by our staff based on input from high school, club and college coaches, as well as media members and members of the basketball community, from across the state. Players are ranked based on their status as a college prospect.\n\nThe primary focus of this first rankings update was to expand the rankings from 65 to 90 players, and also to include more players from smaller schools.\n\nSince the season is still over a week away, this update caused no movement among the top 12 ranked seniors. Several players did, however, move up after raising their stock at preseason events like fall leagues, showcases and the 4<sup>th</sup> Annual Preseason Tournament.\n\n<a href=\"https://www.prepgirlshoops.com/colorado/rankings/2020-rankings/\">Click here to see the full updated list!</a>\n\nHere are the release dates for the other classes:\n\n<em><strong>2021:</strong> Monday, 11/25</em>\n\n<em><strong>2022:</strong> Wednesday, 11/27</em>\n\n<em><strong>2023:</strong> Friday, 11/29 (watch list only)</em>\n\nThese rankings will be updated 2-4 times a year and should become more and more accurate with each update. The next update is scheduled to take place midway through the upcoming prep season.','Colorado 2020 Rankings Have Been Updated!','','publish','open','open','','colorado-2020-rankings-have-been-updated','','','2019-11-22 15:10:47','2019-11-22 21:10:47','',0,'https://www.prepgirlshoops.com/?p=115932',0,'post','',0),
