	(121607,1,'2019-12-09 09:58:27','2019-12-09 15:58:27','<span style=\"color: #800000\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><a href=\"https://www.prepgirlshoops.com/player/jenna-harrison/\">Jenna Harrison</a> (2021)</span></strong></span>\n\n<strong><a href=\"https://www.prepgirlshoops.com/player/jenna-harrison/\">Jenna Harrison</a></strong> is a guard from Kent City. Harrison was not only outstanding in one game last week, but two. <strong>Harrison</strong> scored 27 points (8 three-pointers) against Coopersville and 29 points against Comstock Park. Stay tuned this season to see what <strong>Harrison\'s</strong> point average will be.\n\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt;color: #800000\"><strong>Adelyn Moore (2023)</strong></span>\n\n<strong>Adelyn Moore</strong> is a 5\'8\" guard from Caro. Last week this freshman had an outstanding performance in their win over Marlette. <strong>Moore</strong> scored 26 points and grabbed 15 rebounds. We can expect big things from <strong>Moore</strong> this season.\n\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt;color: #800000\"><strong>Carley Bolen (2020)</strong></span>\n\n<strong>Carley Bolen</strong> is a senior from Tawas. <strong>Bolen</strong> is an asset for the Braves on both offense and defense. Against Roscommon, <strong>Bolen</strong> scored 18 points and had 7 steals.\n\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt;color: #800000\"><strong>Macey Fegan (2023)</strong></span>\n\n<strong>Macey Fegan</strong> is 5\'9\" forward from Standish-Sterling. Last week\'s win against Pinconning was <strong>Fegan\'s</strong> debut on varsity. <strong>Fegan</strong> was an asset to her team by scoring an impressive 22 points.\n\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt;color: #800000\"><strong>Olivia Lowe (2021)</strong></span>\n\nOlivia Lowe is a junior from Leland. In the season opening win against Traverse City, Lowe scored 25 points, grabbed 11 rebounds, and had 7 steals.\n\n<span style=\"color: #800000\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><a href=\"https://www.p