	(124155,1,'2019-12-11 18:31:09','2019-12-12 00:31:09','<b>#1 Seton Catholic 4-0</b>\n\nSeton Catholic had a big win last night against Shadow Mountain. In last weeks Power Ranking, SM was #1 and SC was #2. Now that SC has taken them down, they flip spots. SC is a super deep team and very well coached. They are on a mission after losing a heart breaking game in last years State Finals vs Shadow Mountain.\n\n<b>#2 Shadow Mountain 8-1</b>\n\nAs mentioned above, Shadow lost to Seton and that she why they drop one spot. People may question why they didn’t drop to #3 since Sahuaro is still undefeated. While they do have a better record, I still believe that Shadow is the better team. Shadow will rebound from their loss and continue grinding.\n\n<b>#3 Sahuaro 7-0</b>\n\nSahuaro is now 7-0. This makes them one of the last undefeated squads in the entire conference. This success is largely in part to Alyssa’s Brown, who is having a huge season. Brown is averaging nearly 30 points and 10 rebounds per game!\n\n<b>#4 Saguaro 6-1</b>\n\nSaguaro is having a great season due to their star, Amayah Kirkman. Kirkman is new to the Arizona Basketball scene but she is quickly making a name for herself. Kirkman is averaging nearly 25 points per game and has led her team to a 6-1 record.\n\n<b>#5 Cactus 7-2</b>\n\nCactus is still doing good things. I think they will continue to hover around the 5-7 spot in the rankings throughout the season. <a href=\"https://www.prepgirlshoops.com/player/olivia-lee/\">Olivia Lee</a> and Rose Collup are both doing solid work together, both averaging 12 points per game. As the senior leaders on the team, they are really trying to elevate their squad and so far they’ve done a very good job. Cactus currently has a record of 7-2 and comes in as the #5 team in the 4A Power Rankings.','4A Power Rankings','','publish','open','open','','4a-power-rankings','','','2019-12-11 18:31:09','2019-12-12 00:31:09','',0,'https://www.prepgirlshoops.com/?p=124155',0,'post','',0),
	(124158,1,'2019-12-11 18:41:26','2019-12-12 00:41:26','<b>#1 Millennium 4-1</b>\n\nMillennium lost their first game of the season in a California tournament. In AZ, they are still unbeaten and I believe that they will remain undefeated throughout the season. Millennium makes a strong case for the All-State Power Rankings.\n\n<b>#2 Casteel 4-1</b>\n\nCasteel dropped a game that I thought they should’ve won but that’s basketball. Casteel is still 4-1 and I believe they are still the second best team in the conference. I am looking forward to seeing what this squad can do going forward and how they respond from a loss.\n\n<b>#3 Cactus Shadows 9-1</b>\n\nCactus Shadows is right on Casteel’s heels and I would love to see these teams square off. Cactus Shadows is led by their senior point guard, Brooke Rodgers. Rodgers is having a terrific season and looks fairly dominant, especially getting to the basket.\n\n<b>#4 </b><b>Sunnyslope 6-2</b>\n\nSunnyslope has looked very solid this far into the season. Much like Cactus Shadows, Slope is led by their own senior point guard, <a href=\"https://www.prepgirlshoops.com/player/leslie-aguirre/\">Leslie Aguirre</a>. Aguirre has been playing very well and is gathering a lot of attention from colleges. We’ll see how far Leslie can take Sunnyslope as I believe she is their star.\n\n<b>#5 Buckeye 3-1</b>\n\nBuckeye has had a solid season so far and their only loss has come from Saguaro, another very good team. Buckeye will face a very big test in their next game against Seton Catholic. Winning that game would greatly shake up both the 5A and 4A Power Rankings.','5A Power Rankings','','publish','open','open','','5a-power-rankings','','','2019-12-11 18:41:26','2019-12-12 00:41:26','',0,'https://www.prepgirlshoops.com/?p=124158',0,'post','',0),
